			<sumFormula>Blend of chili peppers, spices, and vinegar (Chili Paste); Chili peppers, tomatoes, and sugar (Chili Sauce); Glutinous rice, fermented soybeans, salt, and sometimes sweeteners (Gochujang)</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Chili pepper paste is a staple in Asian and Mexican cuisine, used as a condiment for extra heat and peppery flavor. It is thicker in texture compared to chili sauce and has minimal ingredients. Chili sauce is typically made from chili peppers, tomatoes, and sugar. Gochujang, or red chili paste, is a staple condiment in Korean cooking, made from glutinous rice, fermented soybeans, salt, and sometimes sweeteners. It is spicy, very concentrated, and pungent in flavor.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">辣椒酱是亚洲和墨西哥菜肴中的主食，用作调料以增加额外的辣味和胡椒味。它的质地比辣椒酱更厚，成分最少。辣椒酱通常由辣椒、番茄和糖制成。韩国料理中的主要调料是韩国辣酱，由糯米、发酵大豆、盐，有时还有甜味剂制成。它的味道辣，非常浓郁，且有强烈的香味。</common:generalComment>
